acosSystemReboot.name: acosSystemReboot
acosSystemReboot.description: The value 'noAction' is always reported in a GET. The value 'rebootSystem' in a SET will cause the box to reboot.

acosHardwareRevision.name: acosHardwareRevision
acosHardwareRevision.description: The hardware revision of the motherboard.

acosSoftwareRevision.name: acosSoftwareRevision
acosSoftwareRevision.description: The software revision of the motherboard.

acosSerialNumber.name: acosSerialNumber
acosSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the motherboard.

acosPartNumber.name: acosPartNumber
acosPartNumber.description: The part number of the motherboard.

acosTotalSlots.name: acosTotalSlots
acosTotalSlots.description: The total number of slots present in the box. This value represents the maximum index into tables that are indexed by slot number.

acosMemoryCapacityTable.name: acosMemoryCapacityTable
acosMemoryCapacityTable.description: This is a table of objects that report the total memory capacity of each type of memory present in the box.

acosMemoryCapacityEntry.name: acosMemoryCapacityEntry
acosMemoryCapacityEntry.description: An entry in the memory capacity table.

acosMemoryCapacity.name: acosMemoryCapacity
acosMemoryCapacity.description: The amount of memory expressed in megabytes. For example, 8 megabytes would be reported as 8.

acosDSPCount.name: acosDSPCount
acosDSPCount.description: The total number of DSP devices present in the box.

acosDeviceTable.name: acosDeviceTable
acosDeviceTable.description: This is a table of devices that are present in the box. The table contains an entry for every slot in the box including empty slots. An empty slot will be reported as 'nimNoDevice' in object 'acosDeviceType'.

acosDeviceEntry.name: acosDeviceEntry
acosDeviceEntry.description: An entry in the device table.

acosDeviceSlotIndex.name: acosDeviceSlotIndex
acosDeviceSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosDeviceType.name: acosDeviceType
acosDeviceType.description: Identifies the unique device type of the card in this slot.

acosDeviceTotal.name: acosDeviceTotal
acosDeviceTotal.description: The total number of devices contained within the slot. This value represents the maximum index into tables that are indexed by a slot device number. Multiple devices can reside in a slot. For example, a slot might contain a dual DS1 NIM consisting of two DS1 interfaces. In MIB tables where both interfaces are accessible, the objects would be indexed through a combination of the slot number and the slot device number. If the slot is empty then 0 is reported for this object.

acosDeviceDescription.name: acosDeviceDescription
acosDeviceDescription.description: A description of the device in the slot. If the slot is empty then a null length string is reported for this object.

acosDeviceTypesAggregate.name: acosDeviceTypesAggregate
acosDeviceTypesAggregate.description: This object contains an aggregate list of the devices present in the box. The list contains pairs of octets, each pair forming a 16 bit integer representing the device type for a slot. Every slot is reported including empty slots. The first octet pair represents slot 1 and the last octet pair represents the highest slot number. The highest slot number can be gotten from object 'acosTotalSlots'. Each octet pair is sent LSB first. The total octets sent will be 2 x acosTotalSlots. The value reported in each octet pair comes from 'AcosDeviceTypeEnum'.

acosDeviceTotalsAggregate.name: acosDeviceTotalsAggregate
acosDeviceTotalsAggregate.description: This object contains an aggregate list of the total number of devices present in each slot. An octet will be sent for each slot including empty slots. The first octet represents slot 1 and the last octet represents the highest slot number. The highest slot number can be gotten from object 'acosTotalSlots'. The total octets sent will be equal to 'acosTotalSlots'. A value of 0 will be reported for empty slots.

acosCpuUtilization.name: acosCpuUtilization
acosCpuUtilization.description: The utilization of the CPU in percent.

acosT1LineConfigTable.name: acosT1LineConfigTable
acosT1LineConfigTable.description: This is a table of configurables for T1 lines.

acosT1LineConfigEntry.name: acosT1LineConfigEntry
acosT1LineConfigEntry.description: An entry in the T1 line config table.

acosT1LineSlotIndex.name: acosT1LineSlotIndex
acosT1LineSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosT1LineSlotInterfaceIndex.name: acosT1LineSlotInterfaceIndex
acosT1LineSlotInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosT1LineBuildOut.name: acosT1LineBuildOut
acosT1LineBuildOut.description: Transmit level attenuation of the T1 line.

acosDS1ChannelConfigTable.name: acosDS1ChannelConfigTable
acosDS1ChannelConfigTable.description: Channel configuration table for a DS1.

acosDS1ChannelConfigEntry.name: acosDS1ChannelConfigEntry
acosDS1ChannelConfigEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 channel config table.

acosDS1ChannelSlotIndex.name: acosDS1ChannelSlotIndex
acosDS1ChannelSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosDS1ChannelSlotDeviceIndex.name: acosDS1ChannelSlotDeviceIndex
acosDS1ChannelSlotDeviceIndex.description: The device number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDS1ChannelIndex.name: acosDS1ChannelIndex
acosDS1ChannelIndex.description: The channel number to configure. For T1 interfaces the valid values are 1..24, and for E1 interfaces the valid values are 1..31.

acosDS1TxChannelControl.name: acosDS1TxChannelControl
acosDS1TxChannelControl.description: Enables or disables the transmit channel on the DS1 on this device in this slot.

acosDS1RxChannelControl.name: acosDS1RxChannelControl
acosDS1RxChannelControl.description: Enables or disables the receive channel on the DS1 on this device in this slot.

acosDS1AggChanConfigTable.name: acosDS1AggChanConfigTable
acosDS1AggChanConfigTable.description: Channel configuration table for a DS1. Channels can be configured in aggregate.

acosDS1AggChanConfigEntry.name: acosDS1AggChanConfigEntry
acosDS1AggChanConfigEntry.description: An entry in the aggregate channel config table.

acosDS1AggChanSlotIndex.name: acosDS1AggChanSlotIndex
acosDS1AggChanSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosDS1AggChanSlotDeviceIndex.name: acosDS1AggChanSlotDeviceIndex
acosDS1AggChanSlotDeviceIndex.description: The device number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDS1TxChannelsAggregate.name: acosDS1TxChannelsAggregate
acosDS1TxChannelsAggregate.description: An aggregate of all transmit channel settings. An octet is sent for each channel on the DS1. For T1 interfaces the total number of octets will be 24, and for E1 interfaces the total number of octets will be 31. The octets are sent starting with the lowest channel and ending with the highest channel. Each octet contains a value representing the state of the channel as follows: 1 = Channel is enabled 2 = Channel is disabled

acosDS1RxChannelsAggregate.name: acosDS1RxChannelsAggregate
acosDS1RxChannelsAggregate.description: An aggregate of all receive channel settings. An octet is sent for each channel on the DS1. For T1 interfaces the total number of octets will be 24, and for E1 interfaces the total number of octets will be 31. The octets are sent starting with the lowest channel and ending with the highest channel. Each octet contains a value representing the state of the channel as follows: 1 = Channel is enabled 2 = Channel is disabled

acosUSIConfigTable.name: acosUSIConfigTable
acosUSIConfigTable.description: This is a table of configurables for a universal serial interface (USI).

acosUSIConfigEntry.name: acosUSIConfigEntry
acosUSIConfigEntry.description: An entry in the USI config table.

acosUSISlotIndex.name: acosUSISlotIndex
acosUSISlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosUSISlotInterfaceIndex.name: acosUSISlotInterfaceIndex
acosUSISlotInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosSDSLConfigTable.name: acosSDSLConfigTable
acosSDSLConfigTable.description: This is a table of configurables for a symmetric digital subscriber line (SDSL).

acosSDSLConfigEntry.name: acosSDSLConfigEntry
acosSDSLConfigEntry.description: An entry in the SDSL config table.

acosSDSLSlotIndex.name: acosSDSLSlotIndex
acosSDSLSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosSDSLSlotInterfaceIndex.name: acosSDSLSlotInterfaceIndex
acosSDSLSlotInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosSDSLInterfaceType.name: acosSDSLInterfaceType
acosSDSLInterfaceType.description: The interface type, Customer Premise Equipment (CPE), or Telephone Company Central Office (CO).

acosEthernetConfigTable.name: acosEthernetConfigTable
acosEthernetConfigTable.description: This is a table of configurables for an ethernet interface.

acosEthernetConfigEntry.name: acosEthernetConfigEntry
acosEthernetConfigEntry.description: An entry in the ethernet config table.

acosEthernetSlotIndex.name: acosEthernetSlotIndex
acosEthernetSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosEthernetFullDuplex.name: acosEthernetFullDuplex
acosEthernetFullDuplex.description: Enables or disable ethernet full duplex mode

acosWANConfigTable.name: acosWANConfigTable
acosWANConfigTable.description: This is a table of common configurables for WAN interfaces.

acosWANConfigEntry.name: acosWANConfigEntry
acosWANConfigEntry.description: An entry in the WAN config table.

acosWANSlotIndex.name: acosWANSlotIndex
acosWANSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosWANSlotDeviceIndex.name: acosWANSlotDeviceIndex
acosWANSlotDeviceIndex.description: The device number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosWANDataLinkProtocol.name: acosWANDataLinkProtocol
acosWANDataLinkProtocol.description: Sets the High Level Data Link Control protocol for this device in this slot.

acosWANSpeed.name: acosWANSpeed
acosWANSpeed.description: Sets the data link speed for this device in this slot.

acosWANSerialStatsTable.name: acosWANSerialStatsTable
acosWANSerialStatsTable.description: This is a table of common serial statistics for WAN interfaces.

acosWANSerialStatsEntry.name: acosWANSerialStatsEntry
acosWANSerialStatsEntry.description: An entry in the WAN serial statistics table.

acosWANSerialStatsSlotIndex.name: acosWANSerialStatsSlotIndex
acosWANSerialStatsSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosWANSerialStatsSlotDeviceIndex.name: acosWANSerialStatsSlotDeviceIndex
acosWANSerialStatsSlotDeviceIndex.description: The device number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosWANTotalRxFrames.name: acosWANTotalRxFrames
acosWANTotalRxFrames.description: The total number of frames received on this port.

acosWANTotalRxOctets.name: acosWANTotalRxOctets
acosWANTotalRxOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this port.

acosWANRxMissedFrames.name: acosWANRxMissedFrames
acosWANRxMissedFrames.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because the receive buffer descriptor ring was empty.

acosWANRxErrorFrames.name: acosWANRxErrorFrames
acosWANRxErrorFrames.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of receive errors.

acosWANRxGlitchErrors.name: acosWANRxGlitchErrors
acosWANRxGlitchErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of receive clock glitch errors.

acosWANRxPllErrors.name: acosWANRxPllErrors
acosWANRxPllErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of receive phase lock loop errors.

acosWANRxLongErrors.name: acosWANRxLongErrors
acosWANRxLongErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because the received frame was too long.

acosWANRxNonOctetErrors.name: acosWANRxNonOctetErrors
acosWANRxNonOctetErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because the received frame was not an integral number of octets.

acosWANRxAbortErrors.name: acosWANRxAbortErrors
acosWANRxAbortErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of abort sequences within the received frame.

acosWANRxCrcErrors.name: acosWANRxCrcErrors
acosWANRxCrcErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of received CRC errors.

acosWANRxOverrunErrors.name: acosWANRxOverrunErrors
acosWANRxOverrunErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of receiver overrun errors.

acosWANRxCdLostErrors.name: acosWANRxCdLostErrors
acosWANRxCdLostErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of lost Carrier Detect.

acosWANTotalTxFrames.name: acosWANTotalTxFrames
acosWANTotalTxFrames.description: The total number of frames transmitted on this port.

acosWANTotalTxOctets.name: acosWANTotalTxOctets
acosWANTotalTxOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this port.

acosWANTxMissedFrames.name: acosWANTxMissedFrames
acosWANTxMissedFrames.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because the transmit buffer descriptor ring was empty.

acosWANTxDiscardedFrames.name: acosWANTxDiscardedFrames
acosWANTxDiscardedFrames.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because the packet was bad, or the link was not ready.

acosWANTxErrorFrames.name: acosWANTxErrorFrames
acosWANTxErrorFrames.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of transmitter errors.

acosWANTxGlitchErrors.name: acosWANTxGlitchErrors
acosWANTxGlitchErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of transmitter clock glitch errors.

acosWANTxUnderrunErrors.name: acosWANTxUnderrunErrors
acosWANTxUnderrunErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of transmitter underrun errors.

acosWANTxCtsLostErrors.name: acosWANTxCtsLostErrors
acosWANTxCtsLostErrors.description: The total number of frames discarded on this port because of transmitter CTS lost errors.

acosWANAtmStatsTable.name: acosWANAtmStatsTable
acosWANAtmStatsTable.description: This is a table of common ATM statistics for WAN interfaces.

acosWANAtmStatsEntry.name: acosWANAtmStatsEntry
acosWANAtmStatsEntry.description: An entry in the WAN ATM statistics table.

acosWANAtmStatsSlotIndex.name: acosWANAtmStatsSlotIndex
acosWANAtmStatsSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosWANAtmStatsSlotDeviceIndex.name: acosWANAtmStatsSlotDeviceIndex
acosWANAtmStatsSlotDeviceIndex.description: The device number of a specific device in the slot. The device numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosWANAtmTotalRxCells.name: acosWANAtmTotalRxCells
acosWANAtmTotalRxCells.description: The total number of ATM cells received on this port.

acosWANAtmClpiRxCells.name: acosWANAtmClpiRxCells
acosWANAtmClpiRxCells.description: The number of ATM cells received on this port with Cell Loss Priority Indication set.

acosWANAtmOamRxCells.name: acosWANAtmOamRxCells
acosWANAtmOamRxCells.description: The number of operation and maintenance ATM cells received on this port.

acosWANAtmEfciRxCells.name: acosWANAtmEfciRxCells
acosWANAtmEfciRxCells.description: The number of ATM cells received on this port with Explicit Forward Congestion Indication set.

acosWANAtmRmRxCells.name: acosWANAtmRmRxCells
acosWANAtmRmRxCells.description: The number of resource management ATM cells received on this port.

acosWANAtmRxCellsDiscarded.name: acosWANAtmRxCellsDiscarded
acosWANAtmRxCellsDiscarded.description: The number of ATM cells received and discarded on this port.

acosWANAtmTotalTxCells.name: acosWANAtmTotalTxCells
acosWANAtmTotalTxCells.description: The total number of ATM cells transmitted on this port.

acosWANAtmOamTxCells.name: acosWANAtmOamTxCells
acosWANAtmOamTxCells.description: The number of operation and maintenance ATM cells transmitted on this port.

acosWANAtmClpiTxCells.name: acosWANAtmClpiTxCells
acosWANAtmClpiTxCells.description: The number of ATM cells transmitted on this port with Cell Loss Priority Indication set.

acosWANAtmEfciTxCells.name: acosWANAtmEfciTxCells
acosWANAtmEfciTxCells.description: The number of ATM cells transmitted on this port with Explicit Forward Congestion Indication set.

acosWANAtmRmTxCells.name: acosWANAtmRmTxCells
acosWANAtmRmTxCells.description: The number of resource management ATM cells transmitted on this port.

acosWANAtmRxHecErrors.name: acosWANAtmRxHecErrors
acosWANAtmRxHecErrors.description: The number of ATM cells received on this port with Header Error Correction errors.

acosDeviceIpAddressTable.name: acosDeviceIpAddressTable
acosDeviceIpAddressTable.description: This is a table of IP addresses associated with devices contained in the box.

acosDeviceIpAddressEntry.name: acosDeviceIpAddressEntry
acosDeviceIpAddressEntry.description: An entry in the device level IP address table.

acosDeviceIpSlotIndex.name: acosDeviceIpSlotIndex
acosDeviceIpSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosDeviceIpInterfaceIndex.name: acosDeviceIpInterfaceIndex
acosDeviceIpInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific device in the slot. The interface numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDeviceIpPortIndex.name: acosDeviceIpPortIndex
acosDeviceIpPortIndex.description: The port number of a specific device in the slot. The port numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of devices reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDeviceIpConnectionIndex.name: acosDeviceIpConnectionIndex
acosDeviceIpConnectionIndex.description: The connection number of a specific device in the slot. The connection numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of allowed connections.

acosDeviceIpAddress.name: acosDeviceIpAddress
acosDeviceIpAddress.description: The IP address assigned to this device in this slot. A value of '0.0.0.0' in a SET will delete the IP address assigned to this device. A value of '0.0.0.0' returned in a GET means the device does not have an IP address assigned to it.

acosDeviceIpAddressSubnetMask.name: acosDeviceIpAddressSubnetMask
acosDeviceIpAddressSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for the IP address assigned to this device in this slot. A value of '0.0.0.0' will be returned in a GET when the device does not have an IP address assigned to it.

acosDeviceIpPeerAddress.name: acosDeviceIpPeerAddress
acosDeviceIpPeerAddress.description: The IP address of the peer for this device in this slot. Note that this object is only accessible if the protocol is set to 'ppp' in object 'acosWANDataLinkProtocol'.

acosRIPControl.name: acosRIPControl
acosRIPControl.description: This object enables or disables the Routing Information Protocol (RIP) for the box.

acosDeviceRipParameterTable.name: acosDeviceRipParameterTable
acosDeviceRipParameterTable.description: This is a table of RIP parameters associated with devices contained in the box.

acosDeviceRipParameterEntry.name: acosDeviceRipParameterEntry
acosDeviceRipParameterEntry.description: An entry in the device level RIP parameter table.

acosDeviceRipSlotIndex.name: acosDeviceRipSlotIndex
acosDeviceRipSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosDeviceRipInterfaceIndex.name: acosDeviceRipInterfaceIndex
acosDeviceRipInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific interface in the slot. The interface numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of interfaces reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDeviceRipPortIndex.name: acosDeviceRipPortIndex
acosDeviceRipPortIndex.description: The port number of a specific interface in the slot. The port numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of ports reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosDeviceRipVersion.name: acosDeviceRipVersion
acosDeviceRipVersion.description: The version of RIP configured for this interface.

acosDeviceRipPoisonedReverse.name: acosDeviceRipPoisonedReverse
acosDeviceRipPoisonedReverse.description: The poisoned reverse configuration for this interface.

acosDNSServerAddress.name: acosDNSServerAddress
acosDNSServerAddress.description: This object specifies the IP address of the Domain Name Server for the box. Zero to disable DNS client functionality

acosDNSTimeout.name: acosDNSTimeout
acosDNSTimeout.description: This object specifies the timeout for replys from the Domain Name Server.

acosBridging.name: acosBridging
acosBridging.description: Enables or disables bridging for all devices. The value 'disabled' in a SET will cause bridging to be disabled on all devices. The value 'enabled' in a SET will cause bridging to be enabled on all devices.

acosBridgeTable.name: acosBridgeTable
acosBridgeTable.description: This table controls bridging on an individual device level.

acosBridgeEntry.name: acosBridgeEntry
acosBridgeEntry.description: An entry in the device level bridging control table.

acosBridgeSlotIndex.name: acosBridgeSlotIndex
acosBridgeSlotIndex.description: The slot number the device resides in. The slot numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of slots reported in object 'acosTotalSlots'.

acosBridgeInterfaceIndex.name: acosBridgeInterfaceIndex
acosBridgeInterfaceIndex.description: The interface number of a specific interface in the slot. The interface numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of interfaces reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosBridgePortIndex.name: acosBridgePortIndex
acosBridgePortIndex.description: The port number of a specific port in the slot. The port numbers range from 1 to the maximum number of interfaces reported in 'acosDeviceTotal' for this slot.

acosBridgeControl.name: acosBridgeControl
acosBridgeControl.description: Enables or disables bridging for this device in this slot.

acosTftpServerAddress.name: acosTftpServerAddress
acosTftpServerAddress.description: The IP address of the TFTP server where upgrade files are stored.

acosTftpAcosName.name: acosTftpAcosName
acosTftpAcosName.description: The filename of the ACOS image that will be read when the box is commanded to upgrade ACOS. If necessary, the name should include the full directory path where the file is stored on the TFTP server (server specific).

acosTftpUpgradeACOS.name: acosTftpUpgradeACOS
acosTftpUpgradeACOS.description: The value 'noAction' is always reported in a GET. The value 'upgradeACOS' in a SET will cause the box to initiate a TFTP session with the IP address of the TFTP server identified in object 'acosTftpServerAddress'. The box will request from the server the file identified in object 'acosTftpAcosName'.

acosTftpApplicationName.name: acosTftpApplicationName
acosTftpApplicationName.description: The filename of the application image that will be read when the box is commanded to upgrade the application. If necessary, the name should include the full directory path where the file is stored on the TFTP server (server specific).

acosTftpUpgradeApplication.name: acosTftpUpgradeApplication
acosTftpUpgradeApplication.description: The value 'noAction' is always reported in a GET. The value 'upgradeApp' in a SET will cause the box to initiate a TFTP session with the IP address of the TFTP server identified in object 'acosTftpServerAddress'. The box will request from the server the file identified in object 'acosTftpApplicationName'.

acosTftpSessionStatus.name: acosTftpSessionStatus
acosTftpSessionStatus.description: This object reports the status of the TFTP client. If a TFTP session has never been active since the box has booted, the value 'ready' is reported. If a session is currently active, the value 'inProgress' is reported. If a session is not currently active, the status of the last active session is reported as 'succeeded' or 'failed'. If the status is 'failed' the object 'acosTftpFailReason' will contain the reason for the failure. If the status is 'failed' or 'succeeded', the object 'acosTftpOctetsRead' will contain the number of octets read.

acosTftpFailReason.name: acosTftpFailReason
acosTftpFailReason.description: The reason for a TFTP failure between the client in the box and a server. If there have not been any failures since the box was last booted, a null length string will be returned. If the last TFTP session succeeded, a null length string will be returned.

acosTftpOctetsRead.name: acosTftpOctetsRead
acosTftpOctetsRead.description: The total number of octets read during a TFTP session. This object is updated periodically by the agent during an active session. This means that if a session is currently in progress, this object can be periodically read by the management station to track the progress of the session. If a session has never been active since the box was last booted, this object will return 0. If a session has failed or succeeded, this object will return the number of blocks read for the failure or success.

acosManagerIpAddress.name: acosManagerIpAddress
acosManagerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the management station to send traps.

acosManagerWriteCommunity.name: acosManagerWriteCommunity
acosManagerWriteCommunity.description: The write community string for the management station allowed to manage the box.

acosTftpFileName.name: acosTftpFileName
acosTftpFileName.description: Identifies the name of the file read by the TFTP client in the box. This object will be sent in traps that report TFTP client activity. This object is not accessible other than when sent in a trap.

acosDhcpEnable.name: acosDhcpEnable
acosDhcpEnable.description: The enable/disable field for DHCP server.

acosDhcpGateway.name: acosDhcpGateway
acosDhcpGateway.description: The default gateway IP address to be returned to the DHCP client.

acosDhcpDnsServer.name: acosDhcpDnsServer
acosDhcpDnsServer.description: The DNS server IP address to be returned to the DHCP client.

acosDhcpSubnet.name: acosDhcpSubnet
acosDhcpSubnet.description: The subnet mask to be returned to the DHCP client.

acosDhcpLowAddress.name: acosDhcpLowAddress
acosDhcpLowAddress.description: The low IP address of the DHCP assignable IP address pool.

acosDhcpHighAddress.name: acosDhcpHighAddress
acosDhcpHighAddress.description: The high IP address of the DHCP assignable IP address pool.

acosDhcpLeaseTime.name: acosDhcpLeaseTime
acosDhcpLeaseTime.description: The lease time in seconds for DHCP assigned addresses. -1 means forever.

acosDhcpDomainName.name: acosDhcpDomainName
acosDhcpDomainName.description: The domain name returned to the DHCP client.

acosDhcpInterface.name: acosDhcpInterface
acosDhcpInterface.description: The logical interface number processed by the DHCP server.

acosDhcpClientTable.name: acosDhcpClientTable
acosDhcpClientTable.description: DHCP Server special handling client table.

acosDhcpClientEntry.name: acosDhcpClientEntry
acosDhcpClientEntry.description: An entry in the DHCP server special handling client table.

acosDhcpClientIndex.name: acosDhcpClientIndex
acosDhcpClientIndex.description: The index number of the DHCP server special handling client table. The index numbers range from 1 to the maximum size of the client table.

acosDhcpClientIpAddress.name: acosDhcpClientIpAddress
acosDhcpClientIpAddress.description: DHCP Server special handling client table IP address. Zero means use an IP address from the address pool.

acosDhcpClientMacAddress.name: acosDhcpClientMacAddress
